JAVASCRIPT NOTES

1. JS console
-allows modification in real-time
-allows to run scripts (in console by inspecting the web page)
-debugging and fixing errors
-modify DOM

2. DOM Manipulation
-change HTML
      document.(html element to be changed).innerHTML="NEW HTML CODE "
-change CSS
      document.(select html element).style="css code"
-perform actions
      use js functions to perform actions on html elements

